    BusinessesPage --> BusinessProfileView: Click on business name
    BusinessesPage --> EditBusiness: Click Edit Business
    BusinessesPage --> AddNewBusiness: Click Add Business
    BusinessesPage --> SuspendBusiness: Click Suspend Business
    BusinessesPage --> BusinessUsersManagement: Click Manage Users
    BusinessesPage --> ImportData: Click Import Data
    BusinessesPage --> ExportData: Click Export Data
    BusinessesPage --> BulkStatusUpdate: Click Bulk Status Update
    
    EditBusiness --> OTPVerification: Submit changes to critical info
    SuspendBusiness --> OTPVerification: Confirm suspension
    AddNewBusiness --> OTPVerification: Submit new business
    BulkStatusUpdate --> OTPVerification: Confirm bulk update
    
    BusinessProfileView --> EditBusiness: Click Edit Profile
    BusinessProfileView --> SuspendBusiness: Click Suspend
    BusinessProfileView --> BusinessUsersManagement: Click Users Tab
    
    BusinessUsersManagement --> BusinessProfileView: Back to Profile
    
    OTPVerification --> BusinessesPage: Verification successful
    
    EditBusiness --> BusinessProfileView: After Save
    EditBusiness --> BusinessesPage: After Cancel
    
    AddNewBusiness --> BusinessesPage: After Submit/Cancel
    SuspendBusiness --> BusinessesPage: After Confirm/Cancel
    ImportData --> BusinessesPage: After Import/Cancel
    ExportData --> BusinessesPage: After Export/Cancel
    BulkStatusUpdate --> BusinessesPage: After Update/Cancel
    BusinessUsersManagement --> BusinessesPage: Back to Business List
    BusinessProfileView --> BusinessesPage: Back to Business List
    
    note right of OTPVerification
        OTP Verification is required for:
        - Adding new businesses
        - Updating critical business information
        - Suspending business accounts
        - Performing bulk status updates
        - Changing subscription plans
    end note
    
    note right of BusinessStatusManagement
        Businesses have four possible statuses:
        - Active: Fully operational
        - Inactive: No recent activity
        - Suspended: Temporarily disabled
        - Terminated: Permanently disabled
        Each status has distinct visual indicators
        and allows different management actions.
    end note
    
    note left of ImportData
        The import process includes:
        1. Template download with format instructions
        2. File upload (Excel or CSV)
        3. Validation with error highlighting
        4. Field mapping confirmation
        5. Final review before import
        6. OTP verification for security
    end note
